<br>
Until a fetus is viable outside of the womb I feel its a potential life. At the point where it can live outside the womb (what is it now adays, about 24 weeks?) I don't think abortions should be allowed, EXCEPT for medically necessary abortions. <br>
<br>
While I was sweating that af when I was raped my mind followed all kinds of possibilites. I didn't think I could do it, but I thought about it. I had the year before was there to listen to a friend who had casual careless sex, took the morning after pill, and still ended up pregnant. And while I probably couldn't have done it, I don't think I could have mentally survived that 9 months. Especially knowing now that I hate being pregnant. I had suffered from depression the year before and was really just getting my life back together. OK, thankfully I didn't have to make this choice. But it was an option that I legally had. <br>
<br>
My sister has had an abortion. She had it done the month before we called to announce we were pregnant with our second child. I am the only family member to know. She and I talked long about it. She knew we were in themiddle of trying to get pregnant. I knew when I came home that she was in trouble. She was just 19. She asked me what she should do. I told her I couldn't answer that, I wasn't her. But no matter her choice I was there 100% with her. I wish duties with the ILS hadn't prevented me from being the one to take her. <br>
<br>
I am not sure she is dealing well with it now. But I shudder to think of what she might have done if the option hadn't been open to her. I don't think she had been at a point where she could have handled pregnancy. And our extended family I think would have pressured her to keep the child (my parents would never do that). So while I don't think she is dealing well with her choice, I think the other choices would have completely undone her at that point of time. But regardless of what I think, it was always her choice. And I firmly stand in her corner on that choice. <br>
<br>
Personal exprience, not really debatable, but this is a personal subject. And my belief its no one else's damn business.<br>
<br>
