As you can tell I have thought about the abortion issue a LOT. I actually tried to refuse testing, but my OB insisted on the level 2 ultrasound because I was 35 at the time. I didn't want an amnio, but after discovering the severe heart defects the fetal specialist strongly recommended it. <br>
<br>
Before the amnio results came in, we were planning to go to term in the hope that the baby could have a transplant (could not have survived with the heart he had - 2 chambers, no septums, malformed valves, etc.) Then the amnio came back T-21 in every cell (Downs) which actually, without the heart defects we might have continued - it's hard to say for sure without having been in that situation. But they told us they don't give donor hearts to Downs babies. Sad, isn't it? <br>
<br>
I think I have really come to terms with the whole situation (it'll be three years next month.) But I can still get worked up over the topic.  This is a decision for families, not lawmakers. <br>
