Someone earlier said pro-choice was pro-abortion and I disagree.  I don’t think it is any of my damn business what you choose to do with your life, your body or your family planning.  I agree that a fetus once viable should not be aborted.  After 25 weeks it can be delivered and turned over for adoption if the mother doesn’t want it.  I disagree that it is the responsibility of our government to restrict people’s legal rights over your arbitrary values, morals or ethics.  Something that gets glossed over in these discussions is the mother’s rights.  You argue that the rights of the baby in cases of rape, incest or other violent sex offenses are somehow less than those of babies conceived by bad planning or just rotten luck.  This ‘evil’ conceptions are abortable while the ‘dumb mom’ ones are not.  What about the woman’s rights?  Are hers less than those of the fetus?  This is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>slavery</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to force her to carry it if she doesn’t want to.  What if the risk to her life is only 20% instead of 80%, does she not have a right?  What if it is 1%?  I am not saying it is an easy decision.  I am not saying it is one I would EVER want to face or that people who face it will have an easy time.  It is terrible, and it is none of my business or yours.  You argue for free agency of gods minions, taking this choice away robs them of that freedom to choose and you are violating your own gods law.  This is the same as China saying their people cannot have more than one kid or Nazi Germany saying the blonde white women had to have as many as possible.  I think Double Latte asked some very important questions and am also interested in your answers Paige.<br>
